Task
Square root of a number
Write a function called squareRoot that takes x as an argument and returns
• square root of x, if x> = 0,
• message "Root of a negative number is NaN", if x <0.
Round the result to two decimal places.
Examples:
• the squareRoot (9) function must return 3;
• the squareRoot (0) function must return 0;
• the squareRoot (-4) function must return "Root of a negative number is NaN".

Solution
function squareRoot (x) {
if (x <0) return "Root of a negative number is NaN";
else return + Math.sqrt (x) .toFixed (2);
}
